{"title":"Macworld Podcast: The U.S. versus Apple","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/2284407/macworld-podcast-the-u-s-versus-apple.html","date":1712219400000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>Apple has filed a civil lawsuit against Apple, and it’s a big one. On this episode of the Macworld Podcast, we talk about the case–what it’s about, why was it filed, what this means to Apple, what it means for users, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is episode 879 with <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Jason-Cross/\" target=\"_blank\">Jason Cross</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Michael-Simon/\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Simon</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Roman-Loyola/\" target=\"_blank\">Roman Loyola</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Listen to episode 879 on Apple Podcasts</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Listen to episode 879 on Spotify</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<h2>Get info </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the links below for more information on what was discussed on the show. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2276150/us-justice-department-lawsit-apple-iphone-monopoly.html\" target=\"_blank\">U.S. Justice Department sues Apple over its “iPhone monopoly”</a> </li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/justice-department-sues-apple-monopolizing-smartphone-markets&amp;xcust=1-1-2284407-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Justice Department Sues Apple for Monopolizing Smartphone Markets (U.S. DOJ)</a> </li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.justice.gov/opa/media/1344546/dl?inline&amp;xcust=1-1-2284407-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Official court filing: U.S. (et al) versus Apple (PDF)</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2